    <note>Liu(2) Ye [1251] Wensou's [3602] son, Tanglao's [3601] grandfather, Zhao(2)'s [1185] brother, Chen's [1225] father. His wives #1 and #2 were both daughters of a Zhao Zhu (sororate), who cannot be identified. His sister's husband was Fan(2) Gao [7024]. SHY:ZG, 27.44b; SS, 262.23b; Yin Zhu, WJ, 13.1b-6b (detailed ancestry back to Later Wei when family moved to Luoyang with the movement of the Wei capital) XTS, 71A.38b traces this ancestry back to the time Han Gaozu married an imperial princess to a Xiongnu chieftain and granted their progeny the surname Liu. CBD, 5, 3899-3900.</note>
